# PZK Project Rules (Unity + Mirror LTS)

## Context & Methodology
- Project: PZK (Multiplayer FPS/TPS)
- Network Framework: Mirror LTS
- Tone: Technical, exhaustive, no fluff.
- Logic: Always use Chain-of-Thought before providing code.

## C# & Unity Standards
- Explicit typing only (No 'var').
- Use XML Documentation (///) for all public members.
- Avoid GC.Alloc in Update/LateUpdate (no LINQ, no new allocations).
- Use `GetComponent` caching in Awake/Start.

## Networking (Mirror)
- Strictly follow the [Command], [ClientRpc], and [TargetRpc] patterns.
- Always check `isServer` or `isLocalPlayer` before sensitive logic.
- Use SyncVars with hook functions for state synchronization.

## Output Requirements
- Never modify unrelated code.
- Provide a "Technical Difference Report" at the end of each response listing:
  1. Modified lines/blocks.
  2. Technical justification (e.g., Sync optimization, GC.Alloc prevention).